sentences: Matia Lenická (born 9 May 1984), also known  by the stage name B-Complex, is a drum and bass producer and DJ from Bratislava, Slovakia.
In 2015, she came out as bi-gender.
B-Complex began producing music in 1996 at the age of 12, being mainly interested in hardcore, trance, and psytrance, moving on to downtempo and hip hop.
Her first UK show was in September 2009 at Matter nightclub in London, for a Hospitality night.
